LESSON  IN  HTML

Q No 1 WHAT IS HTML?

Ans 1
     * HTML stands for Hyper Text Markup Language. 
     * HTML is the standard markup language for creating "WEB PAGES". 
     * HTML describes the "STRUCTGURE" of a Web page. 
     * HTML consists of a series of "ELEMENTS".
     * HTML ELEMENTS TELL THE BROWSER "HOW TO DISPLAY THE CONTENTS".

Q No 2 What is HTML used for?

Ans 2
       * HTML is the code that is used to structure a web page and its content. 
       * For example, content could be structured within a set of paragraphs, 
           a list of bulleted points, 
           or using images 
           and data tables.        

Q No 3 What is the difference between HTML & HYML5?

Ans 3 
      HTML is the primary language for developing web pages. 
      HTML does not have support for video and audio.
      HTML5 is a new version of HTML with new functionalities with markup language with Internet technologies.
      HTML5 supports both video and audio.            